# Multi-Agent RAG Chatbot — Implementation Plan

## Overview

Build a **production-grade multi-agent RAG chatbot** on top of the existing FastAPI skeleton. The system orchestrates multiple AI agents using **LangGraph**, retrieves knowledge from **ChromaDB**, supports **tool calling**, is backed by both **AWS Bedrock** and **OpenAI** as LLM providers, deployed on **AWS** via **Terraform**, and exposed via a **FastAPI** REST API.

---

## Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| API Layer | FastAPI + Uvicorn |
| Agent Orchestration | LangGraph (StateGraph, multi-agent supervisor) |
| LLM Chain Logic | LangChain |
| LLM Providers | AWS Bedrock (Claude 3, Titan) + OpenAI (GPT-4o) |
| Vector Store | ChromaDB (local + persistent) |
| RAG Pipeline | LangChain RAG + ChromaDB retriever |
| Tool Calling | LangChain tools + LangGraph tool nodes |
| **Authentication** | **Dual-layer: API Key + AWS Cognito JWT (RBAC)** |
| Infrastructure | Terraform on AWS (ECS Fargate, ECR, S3, IAM, VPC, Cognito) |
| Containerization | Docker + Docker Compose |
| Config Management | Pydantic Settings + `.env` |

