### 7. Authentication System

> [!IMPORTANT]
> All protected endpoints require either a valid **API Key** (header `X-API-Key`) or a **Cognito JWT Bearer token**. Public endpoints (`/health`, `/auth/token`) are excluded.

#### Authentication Flow

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Two Authentication Methods (both supported):            │
│                                                          │
│  1. API Key (Machine-to-Machine)                         │
│     Header: X-API-Key: <hashed-key>                      │
│     → Validated against DB/env stored hashed keys        │
│     → Role assigned at key creation time                 │
│                                                          │
│  2. Cognito JWT (User-facing / Frontend)                 │
│     Header: Authorization: Bearer <jwt-token>            │
│     → Token issued by AWS Cognito User Pool              │
│     → Verified via Cognito JWKS endpoint                 │
│     → Claims decoded: sub, email, cognito:groups (roles) │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#### Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

| Role | Permissions |
|---|---|
| `admin` | All endpoints: `/chat`, `/ingest`, `/collections`, `/health` |
| `user` | Chat only: `/chat`, `/health` |
| `anonymous` | Public only: `/health` |

#### [NEW] `app/auth/cognito.py`
- Fetches Cognito JWKS from `https://cognito-idp.{region}.amazonaws.com/{pool_id}/.well-known/jwks.json`
- Caches JWKS with TTL (refreshed every 24h)
- Validates JWT: signature, expiry, issuer, audience
- Extracts `sub`, `email`, and `cognito:groups` claims
- Raises `HTTP 401` on invalid/expired tokens

#### [NEW] `app/auth/api_key.py`
- `APIKey` stored with: `key_id`, `hashed_key` (bcrypt), `role`, `name`, `created_at`, `is_active`
- Keys stored in a simple JSON file or env variable for MVP; pluggable to DynamoDB later
- `verify_api_key(plain_key)` → validates hash and returns associated role
- Key generation utility: `generate_api_key()` → returns `prefix.random_secret`

#### [NEW] `app/auth/rbac.py`
- `require_role(*roles)` → FastAPI dependency that checks current user role
- `get_current_user(request)` → tries API key first, then Cognito JWT
- Returns a unified `CurrentUser(sub, email, role, auth_method)` object

#### [NEW] `app/auth/middleware.py`
- Request logging middleware: logs `user_id`, `endpoint`, `auth_method`, `latency`
- Rate limiting per user/IP (configurable via env: `RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE`)

#### [NEW] `app/api/deps.py`
FastAPI dependency shortcuts:
```python
get_current_user         # Any authenticated user
require_admin            # Admin role only
require_user_or_admin    # User or Admin role
```

#### [NEW] `app/api/routes/auth.py`
```
POST /auth/token          → Exchange Cognito credentials for JWT (proxy)
POST /auth/api-key        → Generate a new API key (admin only)
DELETE /auth/api-key/{id} → Revoke an API key (admin only)
GET  /auth/me             → Return current user info from token
```

